This paper focuses on cache-based content delivery in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI) and information theory (IT). The paper also discusses the caching of multimedia content (MM) and the impact of network characteristics (DC) on system performance. Additionally, the paper proposes a protocol for content access, which falls under the category of system and information theory (SI).
